The paper deals with team optimal control of decentralized systems, which is a topic in control theory (cs.SY). The system considered has multiple sub-populations with exchangeable agents, which suggests a possible connection to game theory (cs.GT). The use of mean-field theory and linear quadratic costs also suggests a possible connection to machine learning (cs.MA) and reinforcement learning (cs.LG). Finally, the use of optimal control strategies and the solution of Riccati equations suggests a possible connection to optimization and control theory (cs.AI).
